# 6 Runtime State
## 6.1 Core Component Distinction
1. **RuntimeState**: Immutable snapshot container holding real-time global cognitive context
    - Fields: Active Identity Vector, Current Goal Stack, Ongoing Plan, Reward Baseline, Motivation Energy, Governance Policy Timestamp, Execution History Cursor
2. **SharedRuntimeContext**: Lightweight read-only metadata container passed alongside events, no mutable cognitive state
3. **ServiceLocator**: Static compile-time registry mapping subsystem service IDs to runtime process handles, stateless

## 6.2 Runtime State Snapshot Flow
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    OS[Any Cognitive OS Subsystem] --> RCOS[Runtime Coordination OS]
    RCOS --> SNAP[RuntimeState Snapshot Generator]
    SNAP --> EVENT[Wrapped State Event]
    EVENT --> REK[Runtime Event Kernel]
    REK --> All[All subscribed subsystems receive read-only state snapshot]
```
## 6.2 Key Rule
RuntimeState is read-only to all cognitive subsystems; only Runtime Coordination OS may generate updated snapshots after event processing completes.

Status: ✅ Implemented

