# 8 AI Constitution
## 8.1 Paradigm Shift Away From Static Prompts
Legacy agent safety alignment uses static text prompts injected into LLM context windows, with critical flaws:
- Volatile: Lost on context window overflow
- Unquantifiable: No measurable constraint strength
- Stateless: No persistent runtime enforcement layer

Agent 5.0 redefines AI Constitution as a persistent runtime constraint layer, decoupled from LLM prompt input.

## 8.2 Constitution Runtime Enforcement Flow
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    CONST[AI Constitution Base Embedding] --> VEC[Vector Encoding Pipeline]
    VEC --> VCS[Vector Constraint Space]
    VCS --> G[Governor Supervisor]
    G --> DEC[Candidate Cognitive Decisions]
    DEC --> FILTER[Constraint Validation]
    FILTER --> ACT[Approved Action Pipeline / Rejection Event]
```
## 8.2 Core Capabilities
- Persistent storage bound to Agent Identity Anchor, retained across runtime restarts
- Continuous constraint weighting adjustable via Motivation OS reward signals
- All candidate decisions validated against constitution vectors before execution

Status: 🟡 In Progress (Text constitution implemented, vector encoding pipeline under development)

