# 9 Vector Constitution
## 9.1 Limitations of Rule Lists
Text rule lists are discrete, binary pass/fail checks unable to model continuous gradients of personality, ethics and long-term goals. High-dimensional vector space enables continuous weighted constraint mapping.

## 9.2 Vector Space Encoded Domains
All governance dimensions are embedded into unified high-dimensional vector space:
1. Persistent agent personality traits
2. Long-term core value alignment vectors
3. Multi-layer ethical constraint gradients
4. Dynamic situational behavioral limits
5. User preference compatibility weighting
6. Long-term memory bias correction terms

## 9.3 Future Execution Stack Roadmap (Research Direction)
Once fully engineered, all core cognitive compute layers will operate atop Vector Constitution space:
1. Convolution pattern matching over constraint vectors
2. Attention weight bias injection from constitutional embeddings
3. 2D neural topology layers natively bounded by constitution constraints

Status: 🔵 Research Direction

