# 10 Meta Cognitive Database (MACDB)
## 10.1 Storage Layer Hierarchy Diagram
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    EPI[Episodic Trajectory Shards] --> SEM[Semantic Concept Index Tree]
    SEM --> PAT[Compressed Pattern Library Nodes]
    PAT --> KNOW[Global Knowledge Concept Graph]
    KNOW --> META[Meta-Cognition Reflection Nodes]
    META --> CONCEPT[Unified Concept Embedding Graph]
    CONCEPT --> NEURAL[Neural Cognitive Graph Storage Layer (Future)]
```
## 10.2 Core Definition
MACDB is not a simple key-value memory store. It is a tiered persistent cognitive database designed to retain all symbolic and vectorized cognitive artifacts generated across runtime sessions, serving as the exclusive data source for future neural evolution layers.

## 10.3 Tier Responsibilities
1. Episodic: Raw perception-action trajectory logs
2. Semantic: Indexed abstract concept embeddings for fast lookup
3. Pattern: Reusable action-situation compressed templates
4. Concept Graph: Interconnected relational knowledge storage
5. Neural Graph (Future): Dense low-dimensional feature representations for self-evolution

Status: ✅ Implemented (Symbolic tiers complete; Neural Graph tier planned research)

