# 15 Open Source Vision
## 15.1 Core Community Mission
Agent 5.0 is released under permissive open licensing to establish a shared, community-maintained standard for local autonomous cognitive operating systems. The project rejects closed, cloud-locked agent architectures controlled by single commercial entities.

## 15.2 Stakeholder Alignment
1. Independent Open Source Researchers: Fully accessible cognitive OS reference architecture for AGI safety & cognitive science research
2. Nonprofit Foundations (FUTO, NLnet, Sentient): Local-first privacy-aligned autonomous intelligence stack for grant-funded independent AI research
3. End Developers: Modular, swappable subsystems to build custom autonomous agents unbound to proprietary LLM platforms
4. Individual End Users: Self-hostable persistent cognitive intelligence with full ownership of identity and memory data

## 15.3 Final Statement of Purpose
This project does not aim to build a commercial conversational product or claim artificial general intelligence milestones. Its sole objective is to deliver a transparent, fully open, local-first operating system architecture that enables sustainable, self-governed persistent autonomous AI cognition for global open research communities.

